<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-10-08.12.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80088" speakername="Mr Brian Monteith (Mid Scotland and Fife) (Con)" spid="S2W-10204" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa1008.htm#11" holdingdate="2004-09-29">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what targets it has set for reducing employee numbers in the (a) Civil Service and (b) public sector in each year from 2004-05 to 2007-08.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-10-08.12.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80077" speakername="Mr Tom McCabe" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa1008.htm#11">

  <p>The Scottish Executive is determined to secure operational efficiency in the Civil Service and public sector through ensuring that public servants are in the right job, at the right time and the right place.</p>

  <p>Targets which seek a reduction in employee numbers would play no useful part in this.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-10-08.13.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa1008.htm#12">Sex Offenders</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-10-08.13.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80063" speakername="Mr Kenny MacAskill (Lothians) (SNP)" spid="S2W-10868" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa1008.htm#12" holdingdate="2004-10-06">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how many offenders who have been on the sex offenders&rsquo; register but have not been sentenced to a period of imprisonment have reoffended within a period of (a) six months, (b) one year and (c) two years in each year since 1999.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-10-08.13.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80053" speakername="Cathy Jamieson" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa1008.htm#12">

  <p>Offenders on a sex offenders register cannot be separately identified in the convictions data held on the Scottish Executive Justice Department court proceedings statistical database. Police Force Record Offices operate a variety of recording systems for monitoring and maintaining information on registered sex offenders locally but data from these operational systems cannot be readily extracted for statistical purposes.</p>

</reply>


<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-10-08.14.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80063" speakername="Mr Kenny MacAskill (Lothians) (SNP)" spid="S2W-10872" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa1008.htm#QuestionText" holdingdate="2004-10-06">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive <a name="QuestionText">how many prisoners who have been placed on the sex offenders&rsquo; register and released on licence have reoffended within (a) six months, (b) one year and (c) two years of release in each year since 1999.</a></p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-10-08.14.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80053" speakername="Cathy Jamieson" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa1008.htm#QuestionText">

